comment: Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. Printhead loose --> fixated with tape. T1: 600 µL, Prints not high enough - different depending on position on printhead.

Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. Printhead loose --> fixated with tape. GelMA (T1) and HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + ~400 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2).  Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels). Store in warm ECGM2 until further use.  Prints okay; prints 4 & 6 are slighlty thinner.   Transferring all at the same time into separate 24-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S (230114 MF ).     Note: no cells in GelMA, HUVECS and MSCs are mixed in equal parts into HAMA
